         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">25/6/95. ¶  ¶ The byefollowing seeds (fruits) of Verticordia grandis, dear Dr Dyer, have just freshly arrived from the Murchison-River. ¶ WA. ¶  ¶ I would advise that the ¶  ¶ capsules ¶  ¶ be ¶  ¶ ca...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">95.06.25a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William Thiselton-Dyer</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1891-6, f. 78.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style=""/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Date stamped</seg>: Royal Gardens Kew 30.JUL. 95;<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">annotated in black ink by W. Watson</seg>: 348/1895 (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">i.e. register number in Kew<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </seg>Inwards Book<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">of specimens received</seg>),<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">red ink by W. Hemsley</seg>: Ansd. 3.8.95<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </seg>(<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">letter not found</seg>).</p>
               </note>25/6/95.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The byefollowing seeds (fruits) of Verticordia grandis, dear Dr Dyer, have just freshly arrived from the Murchison-River.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>WA.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I would advise that the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">capsules</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">be</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">cautiously</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">opened</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and the one or more<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">perfect seeds be taken out</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and sown<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">unencumbered</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>by the floral envelopes and be sown in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">sandy-moory soil</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and also sandy-clayey and experimentally also in other mixtures of soil. Naturally this V. and V. oculata grow on sand plains, but their area is very limited and nowhere are they gregarious. If the seeds are liberated for sowing, the seedlings will have the best chance at their earliest state to fix themselves to the soil.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I hope soon to get the fruits also of the indescribably beautiful V. oculata.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M had for some time being trying to introduce this species into horticulture, hoping to do so from seeds<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(M to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Gardeners</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">'</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">chronicle</seg>, 26 November 1877 (B78.02.01), and by<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>having<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>passengers to England carry<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>young plants raised from cuttings (M to W. Thiselyton-Dyer, 7 March 1893<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in ths edition as 93-03-07a)). This<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>latest<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>attempt also failed. Dowe (2023a) discusses M's efforts in a wider context, with images of the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>shrub.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>If you have them once, doubtless these two magnificent V. could be multiplied from cuttings (of not too old wood) with bottom-warmth under a bell-glass</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Always regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Encourage me kindly in letting me know whether you had any success in this promising culture.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Verticordia grandis</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Verticordia oculata</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
      </body>
